The Anambra State Executive Council has approved a Special Academic Calendar for the riverine and flood prone areas in the State. Approving the Special Academic Calendar, the Council considered the request by the State Commissioner for Basic Education, Professor Kate Omenugha, in view of the fact that children from the riverine and flood-prone areas are made to be out of school due to flood, for a significant part of the year covering the first term of thirteen weeks. ALSO READ: Nigeria cannot survive without fundamental restructuring ― ECA scribe Coronavirus: Osun govt screens foreigners in mining sites Obi elated at Okonjo-Iweala’s appointment, recalls her… Ortom donates 35-seater bus, N10m cash to Lobi Stars FC Cultism remains greatest challenge in Ogun — CP According to a statement signed on behalf of the Commissioner by the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry, Mr Linus Nwankwo, made available to Tribune Online on Saturday in Awka, he said the Council approved that the first term of the 2020/2021 academic session will begin on the 3rd August to 4th September 2020 after normal academic activities ends 24th July 2020 and a short break observed 2nd August 2020. He explained that holidays will take place between 7th September to 30th October 2020 and classes resume again on the 2nd November and end on 18th December 2020 and they will advance on Christmas break with others on the 18th of December 2020 to the 4th of January 2021 while they start the second term on the 4th January 2021 with the others. He urged the Chairmen of the Anambra State Post Primary Schools Service Commission, the Universal Basic Education Board, Zonal Directors, Zonal and Area Education Officers, Education Secretaries and all stakeholders in the concerned Education Zones and Local Government Areas to take note of the approval for guidance and necessary action. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HER